Here's an implementation of insertion sort in Java:

```
public static void insertionSort(int[] arr) {
    for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
        int key = arr[i];
        int j = i - 1;
        while (j >= 0 && arr[j] > key) {
            arr[j + 1] = arr[j];
            j = j - 1;
        }
        arr[j + 1] = key;
    }
}
```

To use this method to sort the array `[7, 1, 3, 5, 9]`, you would call it like this:

```
int[] arr = {7, 1, 3, 5, 9};
insertionSort(arr);
System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
```

This would output the sorted array: `[1, 3, 5, 7, 9]`.

